                         n-gram-language-categorization

n-gram based language categorization of text.

note:

put example files in each language for categorization in a directory named
'languages/'.  running './n-gram.apl l' will create files in a directory named
'models/' containing the 300 most common n-grams in each of the languages.  the
names of the language files in the 'languages/' directory define the language
names.

usage:

  ./n-gram.apl [option] [file]

options:

  - l : make n-gram models of all languages
  - p : classify language of a file
  - x : classify language of each paragraph of a thesis xml file
